Five years ago, arguably the greatest entry in Marvel's Cinematic Universe Captain America Civil War made its debut in theaters around the world. Not only did it introduce us to the MCU Spider-Man and Black Panther but the film itself was a masterclass in building on the tension from past films. Half a decade later does the film still hold up? What are the effects the Disney+ shows have on films like this? Is the Winter Soldier water activated? We'll be talking all this and more in this retro review of Captain America Civil War! Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [ComicBookClique.com](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media. Send us feedback at ComicBookClique@Gmail.com! You Are Worthy! Please [SUPPORT US ON PATREON](http://Patreon.com/CBCClubhouse)!

